# Auditor Adversarial Protocol

> **Layer:** Session role — applies when the user asks to **audit**, **verify**, **review shipped work**, or says **"DELIVERED FOR AUDIT"**.
> **Not for:** Executors implementing plans. Executors follow `execution-principles.mdc` §17 + `plan-standards.mdc` §7.
> **Cross-ref:** `plan-standards.mdc` §3b (VERIFY tables), §3c (ADR pivots), §7 (audit ground-checks).
> **Reusable prompt template:** `templates/audit-prompt.md` — fill `{braces}`, paste into new auditor chat.

## Role split (mandatory)

| Role | May say | Forbidden |
|------|---------|-----------|
| **Executor** | `DELIVERED FOR AUDIT` | `SHIPPED`, update checklist to PASS, close plan |
| **Auditor (you)** | `PASS` / `PARTIAL` / `FAIL` per row | Trust executor summary without re-Read; Glob-only existence checks; infer test PASS without running |

**New chat for audit** when possible. Same session as executor inherits optimism.

---

## When this rule activates

User message contains any of: `audit`, `verify against`, `adversarial`, `break it`, `red team`, `DELIVERED FOR AUDIT`, `plan exit verify`, `did I ship`.

If ambiguous, **default to adversarial** — assume the implementation is wrong until proven.

---

## Three phases (all required)

Do **not** skip Phase 2 even if Phase 1 is all PASS.

### Phase 1 — Literal plan VERIFY

1. Read `{{PLANS_PATH}}/NNN-*.md` for the plan under audit.
2. Run **every** step VERIFY row verbatim (`rg`, `Read`, `Glob`, scoped test).
3. Use **`Read` on exact paths** for file-existence claims. **Glob alone is insufficient** (known false negatives in this repo).
4. Paste exit codes for tests. If unable to run: state `BLOCKED — cannot run tests` and mark test rows **INCONCLUSIVE**, not PASS.

Output: table `Step | VERIFY row | Verdict | Evidence (file:line or exit code)`.

### Phase 2 — Break vectors (adversarial)

For **each** vector below, fill: `ATTACK → EXPECT → ACTUAL → VERDICT`.

| # | Vector | What to try |
|---|--------|-------------|
| 1 | **Auth bypass** | Unauthenticated request; session for wsA + path wsB; `X-Target-MNC-Id` mismatch |
| 2 | **Tier / feature bypass** | FREE_TRIAL or tier without required feature; assert **body** not only status |
| 3 | **Route surface** | Negative `rg` for **deprecated** paths across `conf/`, `src/`, `app/`, `test/`, `docs/` |
| 4 | **Caller parity** | Trace SPA → `src/api/*` → `conf/routes` → controller action chain for **every** endpoint in plan |
| 5 | **Scope contract** | Field used by gate/quota/auth must match field in HTTP body (084-class: `parsedRows` vs `entities`) |
| 6 | **Test coverage holes** | List each endpoint/behaviour with **no** scoped IT or named vitest |
| 7 | **Dead code / drift** | Orphan rate-limit rules, stale filters, docs still citing removed APIs |
| 8 | **Edge / UX** | Missing path param guard (`tenantId!`), empty payloads, error message leaks (`e.getMessage`) |
| 9 | **Live endpoint crawl** | If deployment exists: `curl` or `WebFetch` on plan-listed endpoints; compare response shape with SPA caller |

**Minimum output:** 5 break-vector rows. If all PASS, still list **3 residual risks** you attempted but could not exploit.

### Phase 3 — Scoped tests (mandatory when shell available)

```bash
# Plan-listed tests first (use actual paths from plan)
sbt "testOnly <exact.Spec.from.plan>"
npx vitest run <exact.test.file.from.plan>
```

Whole-suite `sbt test` / `vitest run` totals do not substitute for plan-listed scoped tests (`plan-standards.mdc` §3b).

---

## Session Exit VERIFY (7 rows)

Print this table at end of every audit:

| Row | Check | Pass when |
|-----|-------|-----------|
| 1 | Files exist | `Read` exact path succeeds |
| 2 | Encoding | No BOM on edited `.scala` / `.ts` / `.routes` (spot-check) |
| 3 | Scope parity | Gate reads same field caller sends |
| 4 | Negative grep | Deprecated symbols → 0 in `src/` + `conf/` (docs may lag — note separately) |
| 5 | Scoped test | Plan-listed `testOnly` / `vitest` exit 0 |
| 6 | Tracking vs disk | Plan status + `outstanding-tasks.md` + checklist match evidence |
| 7 | Adversarial one-liner | One sentence: "Attacker could … unless …" with `file:line` proof |

SHIPPED is allowed only when rows 1–7 are PASS or ADR-documented pivot (§3c). Auditor does not mark SHIPPED — recommend status to user.

