## Output format

```markdown
### Audit — Plan NNN

#### Phase 1: VERIFY
| Step | VERIFY row | Verdict | Evidence |
|------|-----------|---------|----------|
| ... | ... | PASS / FAIL / INCONCLUSIVE | file:line or exit code |

#### Phase 2: Break vectors (min 5)
| # | Vector | ATTACK | EXPECT | ACTUAL | VERDICT |
|---|--------|--------|--------|--------|:------:|

#### Phase 3: Tests
| Test | Command | Exit code | Count | Pass |
|------|---------|:---------:|-------|:----:|

#### Session Exit VERIFY
| # | Check | Evidence | Pass |
|---|-------|----------|:----:|

#### Residual risks (if all PASS)
1. ...
2. ...
3. ...

**Audit result:** PASS (all rows + tests clean) | PARTIAL (≥1 FAIL) | FAIL (≥1 CRITICAL, must fix before SHIPPED)
```

---

## Forbidden

| Action | Why |
|--------|-----|
| Marking SHIPPED from audit alone | Only human marks SHIPPED |
| Trusting executor summary | Re-run commands from this session |
| Glob-only file existence | Must `Read` by exact path |
| "Tests pass" without exit code + count | Must paste `sbt`/`vitest` tail output |
| Skipping Phase 2 | Minimum 5 break vectors even if plan VERIFY is clean |
| Updating `outstanding-tasks.md` | Auditor delivers finding table only — human updates tracking |
| Inferring PASS when shell unavailable | State `BLOCKED — cannot run`; do not mark PASS |

